Plug-in name: Report
Plug-in shortname: report
Description: Properties Status Report

Most options of the form '-report-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-report-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-report             display a summary of properties status (opposite option
                    is -no-report)

*** DEBUG

-report-debug <n>   level of debug for plug-in Report (default to 0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-report-help        help of plug-in Report
-report-h           alias for option -report-help

*** MONITORING OF PROPERTIES, ERRORS AND WARNINGS

-report-absolute-path  Report absolute path locations (opposite option is
                    -report-no-absolute-path)
-report-classify    Report classification of all properties, errors and
                    warnings (opposite option is -report-no-classify)
-report-exit        Exit on error (set by default, opposite option is
                    -report-no-exit)
-report-output <*.json>  Output -report-classify in JSON format
-report-output-errors <file>  Output number of errors to <file>
-report-output-reviews <file>  Output number of reviews to <file>
-report-output-unclassified <file>  Output number of unclassified to <file>
-report-rules <*.json,...>  Configure the rules to apply for
                    classification,and start monitoring. (preferably use
                    -report-rules="*.json,...")
-report-status      Classify also property statuses (set by default, opposite
                    option is -report-no-status)
-report-stderr      Output detailed textual classification on stderr
                    (opposite option is -report-no-stderr)
-report-stdout      Force detailed textual classification on stdout (opposite
                    option is -report-no-stdout)
-report-unclassified-error <action>  Action to be taken on unclassified
                    errors(default is: 'ERROR') (preferably use
                    -report-unclassified-error="action")
-report-unclassified-invalid <action>  Action to be taken on invalid
                    properties(default is: 'ERROR') (preferably use
                    -report-unclassified-invalid="action")
-report-unclassified-unknown <action>  Action to be taken on unknown
                    properties(default is: 'REVIEW') (preferably use
                    -report-unclassified-unknown="action")
-report-unclassified-untried <action>  Action to be taken on untried
                    properties (default is: 'SKIP') (preferably use
                    -report-unclassified-untried="action")
-report-unclassified-warning <action>  Action to be taken on unclassified
                    warnings(default is: 'REVIEW') (preferably use
                    -report-unclassified-warning="action")

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-report-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from Report to a file. <K> is
                    a combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -report-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-report-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -report-msg-key help to get a list of
                    available categories, and * to enable all categories
                    (preferably use -report-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-report-verbose <n>  level of verbosity for plug-in Report (default to 1)
-report-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for category
                    <k1> to <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use -report-warn-key help
                    to get a list of available categories, and * to enable
                    all categories. Possible statuses are inactive, feedback,
                    warning, error, abort, feedback-once, warning-once,
                    error-once. Defaults to warning. (preferably use
                    -report-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")

*** PRINTING PROPERTY REPORT

-report-csv <name>  if set, output properties as a csv file of the given name
-report-print-properties  print not only the locations, but also the
                    properties themselves (opposite option is
                    -report-no-print-properties)
-report-proven      if set, output proven properties. Otherwise, only
                    unproven ones are shown. (set by default, opposite option
                    is -report-no-proven)
-report-specialized  display properties that are auxiliary instances of other
                    properties. (set by default, opposite option is
                    -report-no-specialized)
-report-untried     display properties which no plug-in tried to prove
                    (opposite option is -report-no-untried)
